<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>MacMurray College follows the guidelines published by the College Board to award AP credit. Credit is awarded based on a score of 3, 4, or 5 and is the equivalent of the credit awarded for similar courses taught on campus. To obtain credit, students must designate MacMurray to receive the official report of AP scores.</i>
